2:T416,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"Article","headline":"Electric Gate Force Testing: What It Is and Why It's the Law","description":"What is gate force testing and why is it legally required in the UK? Learn how we ensure your automated gates are safe and compliant.","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/guides/force-testing-explained/","datePublished":"2026-03-21","dateModified":"2026-03-21","image":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/images/gates/gate-wrought-iron-closeup-scrollwork-detail.png","width":1200,"height":630},"author":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Driveway Gates London","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk"},"publisher":{"@type":"Organization","name":"Driveway Gates London","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk","logo":{"@type":"ImageObject","url":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/android-chrome-512x512.png","width":512,"height":512}},"mainEntityOfPage":{"@type":"WebPage","@id":"https://www.drivewaygateslondon.co.uk/guides/force-testing-explained/"}}3:T60f,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"Is gate force testing a legal requirement in the UK?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. Force testing to BS EN 12445 is required on every automated gate installation under the Supply of Machinery (Safety) Regulations 2008. The installer must document the test results and reference them in the Declaration of Conformity."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What force limits apply to electric driveway gates?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The closing leading edge must not exert a dynamic impact force exceeding 1,400 Newtons or a sustained static crushing force exceeding 400 Newtons. At secondary closing edges and hinge zones, the static force limit is 150 Newtons."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How do I know if my gate has been force tested?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"You should have received a Declaration of Conformity from your installer at handover, which references the force test results. If you do not have this document, ask your installer for a copy. If one cannot be produced, your installation has not been documented as compliant."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Who can carry out gate force testing in London?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Force testing must be carried out by a competent person with appropriate calibrated equipment and knowledge of BS EN 12445. Gate engineers trained and accredited by the Door and Hardware Federation are formally assessed in this methodology."}}]}6:["slug","force-testing-explained","d"]
